                            <comment id="16907453" author="ableegoldman" created="Wed, 14 Aug 2019 17:06:40 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;The fix for this caused a performance regression and is being rolled back. We should look into alternative ways to support concurrent modifications to the underlying data structure&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="17107884" author="ableegoldman" created="Fri, 15 May 2020 03:09:08 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;I think I actually did end up fixing this in a (hopefully!) non-performance-regressing way. Pretty sure it would be fixed for 2.3.1 and 2.4...&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="17107921" author="mjsax" created="Fri, 15 May 2020 04:18:28 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Can you dig out the ticket or PR? And than close this ticket?&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="17108449" author="ableegoldman" created="Fri, 15 May 2020 16:40:46 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;I set the fix version to 2.3.0 rather than 2.3.1, as this issue is technically fixed in 2.3.0. The fix just happened to result in a significant performance regression so a different fix was applied in 2.3.1&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
